			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Very New to Bards<a name="59939"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 1 04 11:57 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you look at them, most instruments are restricted to Secondary, which means you can have the instrument equipped, and nothing else in your hands.
<br />

<br />
Some of the better instruments are Primary, which allows you to equip one in your primary hand, and have a weapon in your secondary.
<br />

<br />
The best instruments are both Primary and Secondary.
<br />

<br />
Nope, can't have two instruments equipped.
<br />

<br />
What you *can* do is get items that have an Instrument Modifier.  The Gem Inlayed Longsword and the Battle Drummer's Main Gauche have Percussion mods, and can substitue for a drum.  The Troubadore's Mace has a brass mod.  You can have two such weapons equipped, and get the benefit from both.
<br />

<br />
There are a few other items out there that have instrument mods.  They tend to be insanely expensive.  A rare exception is the Painted Primal Mask, which has a string mod, and runs around 2000 plat on the server I play on.
<br />

<br />
The Bard Epic has a mod for all types of instruments and for Singing as well.  Good luck in getting it.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
