				<td colspan="2"><span>Well said Liis. 
<br />
    I Twist 4 songs regularly, or as often as I can at least. I used to switch instruments all the time when I was younger, but that decreased gradually as I got better equipment with mods. Now that I have my epic, I don't really *have* to switch out for anything but I don't think a 1.8 mod is that great so I still find myself switching for important moments like a critical mez or extra regen when things are tight. Back in the day, a lot of us learned the basics of instrument twsting when we first learned AEing and swarming. There are some awesome guides on switching instruments and I really encourage folks to check them out and practice, sometimes the smallest things make the biggest difference and you won't really know until it's over. As they say, hindsight is never 20/20, bards are situational, so the more you learn, the better off you and your group are. 
