			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Very New to Bards<a name="60053"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 2 04 10:39 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Before I had my epic, instrument swapping was something that I had to do quite a bit to sing songs that REQUIRED instruments. 
<br />

<br />
Primary hand instruments made this a lot easier, that is for sure.
<br />

<br />
Way back then, there werent many, if any, weapons with instrument mods on them, same for wearable gear.
<br />

<br />
In today's EQ, I highly recommend getting weapons and gear with the required mods if you can afford it, cause instrument swapping SUCKS.
<br />

<br />
Here is how I did/do it.
<br />

<br />
In my hotkey bank, the top 4 slots are for the socials tied to my top 4 songs, I use them to twist (Using hotkeys, not mousing over the buttons)
<br />

<br />
Below that, the next 2 slots are my primary and secondary melee weapons.
<br />
Below that are 2 base inventory slots where I have alternate weapons/instuments.  
<br />
Below that is an open base inventory slot and my assist hotkey.
<br />

<br />
If I need to swap an instument in I just take weapons out and pop in the instrument.  If it is primary hand, it is pretty easy, just put the weapon on the cursor, click it over the primary slot, tap the twist button, and click the weapon back in.  It allows me to melee nonstop while still singing the song I needed the instrument for.  
<br />
It is important to note here that the instrument only needs to be in your hand when you START the song, once the song is started, you can swap the weapon back in.
<br />
If the instrument is secondary melee only, then it takes a few more clicks, swap the primary weapon to an open inventory slot, pick up the instrument, click it in, start the song, click the weapon back in, drag the primary weapon back over.  It takes a little bit of practice to make it smooth.
<br />
 </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
